<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> - In the previous patch, Level 60 became a full level, when it had been half a half level the day before.<br>
<br>
- &quot;Penalty levels&quot; have once again been rebalanced such that level 60 is much closer to the half level that it was before, and experience was instead redistributed throughout the earlier levels.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If exp at 60 is at about half a level, then to me it follows that all 60s will need to gain another half level to ding 61. Which probably won't take that long *laughs*.<br>
<br>
Eveningsong<br>
57 Teller of Tales, Morell-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/uplethra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Plethra</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Looting Highpass</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#628CBC>(10/14/02 1:32:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=601.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: With POP</span><hr size=1> It really isn't the best way to take all that exp away from peeps, even if it was relatively &quot;easy&quot;.  However, it really isn't fair to just let all lvl 60's ding in 1 kill either.  They should extend the lvl 60 exp pool, say, double it or even triple it and apply your current exp in 60 to that pool.  <br>
<br>
If you had full 60 exp on the day PoP is released, you will be granted 50% of lvl 60 and have to complete the other half to ding 61 (or given 33% if they would triple it).  Which, if your 60, really isn't too much to ask on either party.  VI doesn't get lvl 60's dinging instantly and we are not penalized for having full 60 exp. <p><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7675">Master Plethra</a><br>60 Phantasmist<br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7726">Lickety Splits</a><br>51 Disciple<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/udraekk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Draekk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#628CBC>(10/14/02 1:48:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=601.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: With POP</span><hr size=1> That quote you used is from when they rebalanced &quot;hell&quot; levels through 51-60. As a result of 51,54,55,59 taking less xp to get through, level 60, which previously was an extremely easy level, took more xp to get through. This &quot;balanced&quot; the post 50 experience and fairly effectivly eliminated &quot;hell levels&quot;.<br>
<br>
My money is betting on them not touching level 60. I dont have any evidence from VI one way or the other, but the way I see it, there's just no reason to do it. 61-65 will have it's own set of experience rules and whatnot, I couldnt understand why they would bother changing anything pre-61. If they DID do something which lowered xp for people who are lvl 60, they're only delaying the leveling process by a matter of a few hours.<br>
<br>
PS. In regards to the 50-60 jump: I started playing EQ when MT came up so I dont know first hand.. I've heard both sides, that people who were full in 50 gained lvl 51 after only a kill or two; and that people who were lvl 50 lost a significant amount of xp and had to regain that before they could level. I'll just have to wait and see for PoP. Either way, it's really not a big deal. <p><font size="1"><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22691" style="text-decoration:none">Profile</a>  -  <a href="http://www.furys-edge.com" style="text-decoration:none">Fury's Edge</a></center></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elderan>Elderan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#628CBC>(10/14/02 2:36:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=601.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   This is what happened last time...</span><hr size=1> Last time the levels were increased they decreased the amount of exp someone had to just below that of 51. If I remember correct I had to kill about 3-4 mobs before I leveled from 50-51. <br>
